---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Install" description="Drop Deliberate into your project. Works with Claude Code, Cursor, Codex, Gemini, or any agent that reads markdown.">
  <section class="install-hero">
    <div class="container container-prose">
      <div class="eyebrow">Install</div>
      <h1 class="install-title">Drop it in. Reference it. Ship.</h1>
      <p class="install-lede">
        Deliberate is plain markdown. No build step, no dependencies, no lock-in. Works with any agent that can read a file.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="install-body">
    <div class="container container-prose">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num mono">01</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h2 class="step-title">Copy the files into your repo</h2>
          <p class="step-p">Clone or download from GitHub and copy <code>deliberate.md</code> and the <code>skills/</code> directory into your project root.</p>
          <pre><code># Quick option - clone, copy, done
git clone https://github.com/angad729/deliberate.git /tmp/deliberate
cp /tmp/deliberate/deliberate.md ./
cp -r /tmp/deliberate/skills ./</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num mono">02</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h2 class="step-title">Point your agent at them</h2>

          <h3 class="tool-title">Claude Code</h3>
          <p class="step-p">Create or update <code>CLAUDE.md</code> at your project root:</p>
          <pre><code># CLAUDE.md

Follow the guidelines in @deliberate.md for all code changes.
When working on features against a PRD or design doc, also follow @skills/spec.md.
When debugging, also follow @skills/debug.md.
When reviewing PRs, also follow @skills/review.md.
When writing tests, also follow @skills/test.md.
When crossing component boundaries, also follow @skills/architect.md.
When planning a migration, also follow @skills/migrate.md.
When responding to an incident, also follow @skills/incident.md.</code></pre>

          <h3 class="tool-title">Cursor</h3>
          <p class="step-p">Drop files into <code>.cursor/rules/</code> as <code>.mdc</code> rules, or reference them from <code>.cursorrules</code>:</p>
          <pre><code># .cursorrules

Always follow the guidelines in deliberate.md.
When the task matches a specialized skill in skills/, follow that skill as well.</code></pre>

          <h3 class="tool-title">Codex / Gemini / other agents</h3>
          <p class="step-p">Include the files in your project context or system prompt. Plain markdown works everywhere.</p>

          <h3 class="tool-title">Paste-in fallback</h3>
          <p class="step-p">No config? Paste the contents of <code>deliberate.md</code> into your agent's system prompt or custom instructions. Done.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num mono">03</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h2 class="step-title">Load skills situationally, not all at once</h2>
          <p class="step-p">
            <code>deliberate.md</code> is the default load. Pull in a specialized skill only when the task calls for it:
          </p>
          <ul class="situational">
            <li><strong>Starting a feature from a PRD?</strong> → <a href="/skills/spec/"><code>/spec</code></a></li>
            <li><strong>Fixing a bug?</strong> → <a href="/skills/debug/"><code>/debug</code></a></li>
            <li><strong>Reviewing a PR?</strong> → <a href="/skills/review/"><code>/review</code></a></li>
            <li><strong>Writing tests?</strong> → <a href="/skills/test/"><code>/test</code></a></li>
            <li><strong>Shaping boundaries or contracts?</strong> → <a href="/skills/architect/"><code>/architect</code></a></li>
            <li><strong>Planning a migration?</strong> → <a href="/skills/migrate/"><code>/migrate</code></a></li>
            <li><strong>Production is on fire?</strong> → <a href="/skills/incident/"><code>/incident</code></a></li>
          </ul>
          <p class="step-p muted">Loading every skill for every task defeats the point - each skill is a lens, and too many lenses at once blurs the focus.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <div class="install-when-not">
        <div class="eyebrow">When not to use it</div>
        <ul class="when-not-list">
          <li><strong>Trivial one-liners.</strong> Deliberate biases toward caution over speed. For throwaway scripts or obvious edits, the overhead isn't worth it.</li>
          <li><strong>Rapid prototyping where correctness doesn't matter yet.</strong> Plan-first gets in the way of exploration.</li>
          <li><strong>You disagree with a principle.</strong> Fork it. Delete sections. Rewrite for your taste. Starting point, not scripture.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .install-hero {
    padding: 5rem 0 3rem;
  }
  .install-title {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4vw, 3.25rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .install-lede {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .install-body {
    padding: 2rem 0 5rem;
  }

  .step {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 3rem 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }
  .step-num {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--forest-600);
    font-weight: 500;
    padding-top: 0.375rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .step-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .step-p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .tool-title {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.625rem;
    color: var(--forest-800);
  }
  .step pre {
    margin: 0.75rem 0 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
  }

  .situational {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }
  .situational li {
    padding: 0.625rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-soft);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }
  .situational li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .situational strong { color: var(--ink); }

  .install-when-not {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
    background: var(--forest-50);
    border-radius: 6px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--forest-500);
  }
  .when-not-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  .when-not-list li {
    padding: 0.625rem 0;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--forest-800);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .when-not-list li strong { color: var(--forest-900); }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .step { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.5rem; }
    .step-num { font-size: 0.875rem; }
  }
</style>
